===Research===
The school houses National Centers of Research Excellence including the National Center for Medical Readiness; the Lifespan Health Research Center, which houses the nation’s largest and oldest study of human growth and development; the [[Wright State University and Premier Health Partners Neuroscience Institute at Miami Valley Hospital]]; and the Center for Interventions, Treatment, and Addictions Research.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.med.wright.edu/research/|title= Research at Boonshoft School of Medicine|accessdate=2011-07-01}}</ref> In fall 2007, five researchers associated with the Neuroscience Institute won a prestigious Program Project Grant from the [[National Institute of Neurological Disorders and Stroke]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.med.wright.edu/whatsnew/2007/ppg|title= Prestigious $4.8 Million Grant Advances Neuroscience Research|accessdate=2009-08-23}}</ref> The $4.8 million grant is the first Program Project Grant Wright State University has received. In the [[fiscal year]] of 2010, Wright State University received 610 research awards for a total of $94,111,241. The region’s leader in [[biomedical research]], the Boonshoft School of Medicine received 158 awards for a total of $22,440,827 during that same time period.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.med.wright.edu/research/summary|title= Boonshoft School of Medicine Research and Sponsored Program Funding|accessdate=2011-07-01}}</ref> Federal grants were received from the [[Department of Health and Human Services]] and various National Institutes of Health, the [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]], [[NASA]] and the [[United States Department of Education|Department of Education]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.med.wright.edu/research/summary|title= Boonshoft School of Medicine Research and Sponsored Program Funding|accessdate=2011-07-01}}</ref>

The Department of Community Health at Boonshoft School of Medicine ranks 10th out of 129 accredited M.D.-granting U.S. medical schools for the total amount of [[research funding]] it has received from the [[National Institutes of Health]] in the area of Public Health and Preventive Medicine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.med.wright.edu/about/characteristics|title= National ranking for research in public health|accessdate=2009-09-14}}</ref>

