The [[National Center for Medical Readiness]] (NCMR), housed at the Boonshoft School of Medicine, is a response organization for large scale emergencies, such as a weather disaster, terrorist attack or hazmat situation. The Center was established by the Wright State University Boonshoft School of Medicine Department of Emergency Medicine and has been certified as a [[National Disaster Life Support Foundation]] (NDLSF) Regional Training Center.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medicalreadiness.org|title= National Center for Medical Readiness|accessdate=2009-11-05}}</ref>

